page.title: 14Whiteparish common
page.content: Whiteparish common is an area of woodland on the northern boundary of our Domesday area.Many varieties of insects and birds live there. On Whiteparish common there are some rare butterflies ,one of these is the White admiral.The white admiral has got spotted wings of white with bands of white on them as well.Its wing span is about 6 cm.The female is slighty larger and it is a lighter colour.On the fore wings there are three white spots between the band of white ,and the edges are fringed with black and white.It hibernates inside a folded honeysuckle leaf it is sucured to the stem by silken threads.It looks rather like the Purple Emporer.The under side of the wings is very pretty.The egg is olive green in colour and it is in the shape of an orange.At the top of the egg it is sort of flat.
